pr_title: Rewrite Models and subsequently Routes in Typescript
pr_body:
Closes #1757 

#### Tasks Done:
- [x] Rewrite Models in Typescript
    - Sequelize currently does not currently handle foreign keys in the best way possible in Typescript
    - I discussed this with the community and maintainers on their Slack and have used the best possible solution as of now according to our discussion [here](https://sequelize.slack.com/archives/C0CELV3N1/p1644759779263599), can be accessed once you join their workspace using their inviter bot [here](https://github.com/sequelize/sequelize#book-resources).
    - An issue has also been opened based on our discussion  https://github.com/sequelize/sequelize/issues/14125
- [x] Rewrite controllers for the routes in Typescript
    - Made some minor typing tweaks and they were fixed
    - One specific unique handling case was required in the `routes/payment.ts` where we had to mask the `cardNum` property using `*` hence had to be converted to string. To solve this, a new interface `displayCard` has been created just for this specific use case.

Rebased my branch just before opening the Pull Request to make sure it's up-to-date.

#### The commits are as follows:
- [Commit 1](295f89b1105b28a3b013667e8dd98fb2939cd57f): Convert Models to class-based typescript
- [Commit 2](295f89b1105b28a3b013667e8dd98fb2939cd57f): Fix the typings in `datacreator.ts` and update models wherever required
- [Commit 3](19edb5ee6a782d944a6c626996528f2db1901ec7): Fix the typings in the `routes/` directory related to the models
- [Commit 4](6a1936289c196b6815bb8c37c492a26817725b01): Cleanup unused imports and commented out code from `models/`
- [Commit 5](299ec4252d46a06682a1923dd3693123dd184366): Used the `npm run lint:fix` to lint the files and one type conversion from string to number

Edit: Commits continued while fixing the CI bugs hence lost track. The above are invalid now, but the PR is finally valid including the CI checks :))

pr_title: Rewrite Models and subsequently Routes in Typescript
pr_body:
Closes #1757 

#### Tasks Done:
- [x] Rewrite Models in Typescript
    - Sequelize currently does not currently handle foreign keys in the best way possible in Typescript
    - I discussed this with the community and maintainers on their Slack and have used the best possible solution as of now according to our discussion [here](https://sequelize.slack.com/archives/C0CELV3N1/p1644759779263599), can be accessed once you join their workspace using their inviter bot [here](https://github.com/sequelize/sequelize#book-resources).
    - An issue has also been opened based on our discussion  https://github.com/sequelize/sequelize/issues/14125
- [x] Rewrite controllers for the routes in Typescript
    - Made some minor typing tweaks and they were fixed
    - One specific unique handling case was required in the `routes/payment.ts` where we had to mask the `cardNum` property using `*` hence had to be converted to string. To solve this, a new interface `displayCard` has been created just for this specific use case.

Rebased my branch just before opening the Pull Request to make sure it's up-to-date.

#### The commits are as follows:
- [Commit 1](295f89b1105b28a3b013667e8dd98fb2939cd57f): Convert Models to class-based typescript
- [Commit 2](295f89b1105b28a3b013667e8dd98fb2939cd57f): Fix the typings in `datacreator.ts` and update models wherever required
- [Commit 3](19edb5ee6a782d944a6c626996528f2db1901ec7): Fix the typings in the `routes/` directory related to the models
- [Commit 4](6a1936289c196b6815bb8c37c492a26817725b01): Cleanup unused imports and commented out code from `models/`
- [Commit 5](299ec4252d46a06682a1923dd3693123dd184366): Used the `npm run lint:fix` to lint the files and one type conversion from string to number

Edit: Commits continued while fixing the CI bugs hence lost track. The above are invalid now, but the PR is finally valid including the CI checks :))

pr_body:
Fixes #1758 
Migrated the lib/insecurity.js

However, when running `npm run frisby`, 5 of the test files i.e 14 test cases were failing. Trying to debug now hence opened a draft PR for now

This PR 
- introduces Cypress as a dev dependency
- adds it in the Github CI through cypress-action and tests in 3 environments:
  - Edge on Windows
  - Chrome on Linux
  - Firefox on Linux 
- removes the example test spec files that come in the bundle
- and adds a placeholder testspec that basically checks visibility the Juice Shop homepage.

The CI passes successfully too! 🎊

pr_title: Migrate PrivacyPolicy & DirectAccess tests to Cypress
pr_body:
The PR has 5 atomic commits:
- a5daa70: Migrates the `expectChallengeSolved` from e2eHelper to a custom Cypress command by calling the API `/api/Challenges/?name=` directly drastically reducing the time spent on visiting the scoreboard everytime to check if the challenge is solved or not
- a4fa118: Migrates the Privacy Policy spec in Cypress test suite and removes the legacy one
- d30ae12: Migrates the Direct Acess spec in Cypress test suite, removes the legacy one, and its relevant helper functions that require a node environment in the form of cypress tasks
- c4c3645: Removes the placeholder spec file merged earlier for CI simulation
- 358074f: Pins the angular cli dependency in the CI as suggested and done initially by @J12934

pr_title: Split challenge utils to another file
pr_body:
Since the utils.ts file grew a bit large and for easier use of `utils.ts` in the future for imports in Cypress, this PR migrates the following methods from `utils.ts` to a new `challengeUtils.ts`:
- solveIf()
- solve()
- sendNotification()
- notSolved()
- findChallengeByName()
- findChallengeById()
- solveFindIt()
- solveFixIt()

And all the files where these methods were imported have been updated accordingly with the following code snippet skeleton:
```diff
     import utils = require('../lib/utils')
+    import challengeUtils = require('../lib/challengeUtils')

-    utils.notSolved(challenges.xxeDosChallenge)
+    challengeUtils.notSolved(challenges.xxeDosChallenge)
```

Let me know if we should add some more(the CTF ones) or remove anything from here

pr_body:
This PR introduces 
- cy.login custom command
- GetFromConfig task to get a value using the config npm package
- GenerateAuthenticator task to get OTPlib authenticator

And with the help of all these, the following tests have been migrated:
- publicFtpSpec
- redirectSpec
- tokenSaleSpec
- loginSpec
- administrationSpec
- changePasswordSpec
- dataExportSpec
- deluxeSpec
- forgotPasswordSpec
- metricSpec

The last commit also introduces:
- Latest ways to add cypress environment variables
- sets cookies to disable "welcome to juice shop" & "cookies" overlay and the beginning of each test

🚫 Lazy typo fixing PRs - if you fix a typo in a file, your PR will only be merged

🔅🔅🔅🔅🔅🔅🔅🔅🔅🔅🔅🔅🔅🔅🔅🔅🔅🔅🔅🔅🔅🔅🔅🔅🔅🔅🔅🔅🔅🔅🔅🔅🔅-->

### Description
Replaces the 3 similar actions to a GitHub matrix that includes:
- 2 OS:
  1. Ubuntu
  2. MacOS  

- 2 browsers:
  1. Chrome
  2. Firefox  

The reason for not going ahead with Windows is:
- Firefox doesn't even get detected by cypress
- Edge weirdly gets a massive 60 second timeout on our localhost server requests itself
- Chrome is flaky on windows

The above is on the basis of a few actions ran on my fork as well as on our previous PRs. This matrix should also be robust and cut down the flakiness massively.

### Affirmation
- [x] My code follows the [CONTRIBUTING.md](https://github.com/juice-shop/juice-shop/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md) guidelines

This PR introduces:
- `defaultCommandTimeout` across the test suite set to 10 seconds
- `baseUrl` as a Cypress env to be accessed by the DOM elements
- And the following helper Cypress tasks:
  - `GenerateCoupon(discount: number)`: returns security.generateCoupon(discount)
  - `GetCouponIntent()`: returns the couponIntent from the chatbot training data
  - `GetFromMemories(property: string)`: returns the req property of the memory using config
  - `disableOnContainerEnv()`: returns utils.disableOnContainerEnv();
  - `disableOnWindowsEnv()`: returns utils.disableOnWindowsEnv();

And with the help and use of above, migrates the following test spec files broken down into atomic commits:
- scoreboard spec
- geostalking spec
- b2bOrder spec
- chatbot spec
- forgedJwt spec
- profile spec
- basket spec
- datErasure spec
- nosql spec
- totp spec

Tested them locally and all succesfully pass at the first attempt:
![Screenshot_2022-06-24-19-06-24_3280x1080](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/55556994/175548827-61a50198-17fb-4ac4-8f72-d8d77d334cb0.png)
